summary:
The Security Council:

* Decides that all Ivorian parties take steps to ensure free, fair, and transparent general elections;
* Requests the Secretary-General to designate a High Representative for the elections in Côte d’Ivoire to assist the Independent Electoral Commission and Constitutional Council;
* The High Representative's mandate includes verifying the electoral process, providing advice and guidance, and reporting to the Security Council;
* The High Representative's mandate will end after the general elections;
* Calls upon donors to provide financial resources to support the High Representative's mission;
* Takes note of the disarmament, demobilization, and reintegration (DDR) process agreement and demands its full implementation;
* Extends the mandate of UNOCI and French forces until 24 June 2005;
* Authorizes the Secretary-General to plan for a potential increase in UNOCI's authorized strength;
* Urges donors to support the implementation of the Pretoria Agreement;
* Calls upon parties to cooperate with UNOCI and guarantees its personnel's safety and security;
* Welcomes efforts to implement the Secretary-General's zero-tolerance policy on sexual exploitation and abuse;
* Requests regular reports from the Secretary-General, France, and the African Union on the situation in Côte d’Ivoire. 
* Expresses full support to the Special Representative of the Secretary-General and decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
